entry.title: [fix-swo-violations] Fix sort comparison function
entry.content:
DownloadComparator assumes that its arguments do not alias the same

object. This assumption is used to check that IDs are unique.

However, this assumption is not guaranteed to hold by std::sort, and

the CHECK fails if _LIBCPP_DEBUG_STRICT_WEAK_ORDERING_CHECK is defined.

This CL gets rid of the assumption and only checks for uniqueness if

left-hand and right-hand sides of the compare function are different

objects.

entry.title: [ios] Capture a video stream using getUserMedia
entry.content:
In CLs[1][2][3][4][5], a base code for capturing video streams with

iPhone camera has landed. In this CL, the video settings are adjusted

so that video streams can be captured.



Since Mac and iOS share most of their implementations, testing code on

both platforms is important.



For iOS, this code has been tested manually on an iPhone 13 running

iOS 16.5.

In the current implementation,

1. video capture is unaware of device orientation and

2. commandline switches are required to make Video capture work on iOS



TEST: ios-deploy --justlaunch --bundle \

out/Debug-iphoneos/content_shell.app --args=" \

--auto-accept-camera-and-microphone-capture \

--disable-video-capture-use-gpu-memory-buffer \

https://webrtc.github.io/samples/src/content/getusermedia/gum/"



As a precaution, for mac users, the code flow is manually tested using

the below commands



TEST: ./out/debug/Content\ Shell.app/Contents/MacOS/Content\ Shell \

--auto-accept-camera-and-microphone-capture \

--disable-video-capture-use-gpu-memory-buffer \

https://webrtc.github.io/samples/src/content/getusermedia/gum/



./out/debug/Chromium.app/Contents/MacOS/Chromium \

--disable-video-capture-use-gpu-memory-buffer \

https://webrtc.github.io/samples/src/content/getusermedia/gum/



[1]https://crrev.com/c/4473569 : [ios] Add iOS capture support (1/n)

entry.title: Make FontBuilder::CreateFont() lazier.
entry.content:
FontBuilder has a bit mask of font properties that are set, and only

does a hash table lookup to find the right font if any of them are.

However, we can be even lazier; if the set properties all match what

was already in the ComputedStyleBuilder, we can do an early abort.



This could happen if, for instance, we had a rule like



* { -webkit-font-smoothing: antialias; }



Every element will get font-smoothing: antialias, but only the root

element actually needs to change fonts over it. Of course, it's better

to set such a rule on the root, but there are many similar patterns

that are not as easy to get around.

entry.title: Annotate Cross task dangling pointers detected on Linux builds
entry.content:
This adds the DanglingAcrossTasks keyword and annotates raw_ptrs that

are "dangling cross task", i.e. that are freed and released in

different tasks.

These are more likely to allow UAFs and therefore are prioritized

over other dangling raw_ptr (Those remaining with DanglingUntriaged).



Protocol used:

1. Apply automatic dangling pointer annotation: crrev.com/c/4474553

2. Disable "DanglingUntriaged":

``` base/allocator/partition_allocator/pointers/raw_ptr.h:

constexpr auto DanglingUntriaged = base::RawPtrTraits::kEmpty ```

3. Configure Dangling pointer detection for cross tasks detection and logging only.

4. Run all tests using https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AMMERcqy0eafFWopUCHYsIKIKEp3J8DFxqW9UIbzIHo/edit?pli=1&resourcekey=0-e12-tlqsWfAOkle97uWw3w

5. Concatenate and filter output:

``` cat output_* | sort -nr | uniq | sed -e 's/\(.\)Found/\1\nFound/g' | grep -a -e "../../" | sed 's_^.*\.\./\.\./__' | sort | uniq > test_output_all

6. Apply the annotation using https://docs.google.com/document/d/1SGMZAaoEb6J0-NQO5V07TShxGAL5bxVN08TylBOrSCw/edit?usp=sharing

entry.title: Introduce SharedDictionaryNetworkTransaction
entry.content:
This CL introduces SharedDictionaryNetworkTransaction and

SharedDictionaryNetworkTransactionFactory. They are used to deocode

shared dictionary compression.



When `NetworkContextParams.shared_dictionary_enabled` flag is enabled,

NetworkContext::MakeURLRequestContext() sets a

CreateHttpTransactionFactoryCallback which creates a

SharedDictionaryNetworkTransactionFactory with

ThrottlingNetworkTransactionFactory.



URLRequestHttpJob::StartTransactionInternal() will calls the

CreateTransaction() method of the TransactionFactories. And the layering

of HttpTransactions will be like this:

URLRequestHttpJob

=> HttpCache::Transaction

=> SharedDictionaryNetworkTransaction

=> ThrottlingNetworkTransaction

=> HttpNetworkTransaction



SharedDictionaryNetworkTransaction registers a callback with the

underlying transaction that will be called just before the request is

sent to the network. When this callback is called, it tries to get a

registered dictionary from SharedDictionaryManager. If a matching

dictionary is found, and the "content-encoding" header of the response

from the server is "sbr", it will decode the response body using a

BrotliSourceStream with the dictionary.



URLLoader sets SHARED_DICTIONARY_ORIGIN_CHECK_REQUIRED flag to NoCors

requests. And the flag is set, SharedDictionaryNetworkTransaction checks

the response header's "Access-Control-Allow-Origin" before using the

dictionary. And if there is no appropriate value is set, the request

will fail with net::ERR_DICTIONARY_ORIGIN_CHECK_FAILED error.



Bug: 1413922
